➡️12% of the world’s wheat exports

content: Ukraine and Russia account for nearly 30% of the world’s wheat, 17% of corn and over half of sunflower seed oil exports. These have been drastically reduced by war. Worse, FAO estimates that 20-30% of this year’s crop won’t be planted because of war. A global food crisis looms.
